### TCODE: 
#### SU24 (Maintain Authorisations Values)

-> This transaction is used to maintain authorisation default values and check indicators for transactions, reports, and other applications.

-> The values maintained in the SU24 are automatically pulled during role building in PFCG.

##### Purpose:
- Maintain authorization objects checked by a transaction.
- Define default authorization values.
- Control which authorization objects are proposed during role creation in PFCG.

##### Work Flow
    Create / identify transaction (Auth Obj: V_VBAK_VKO)
            |
    Assign in SU24 Under transaction code drop down
            |
    Maintain Authorization proposals in SU24 (set Indicator to Check/maintain, proposal status: Y or N, if not taken automatically)
            |
    Assign authorization values
            |
    It will ask for Transport (Create a WorkBench TR and move the changes to capture the changes).
            |
    Generate roles in PFCG
            |
    Assign roles to user
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

##### Check Indicators:
1. Check/Maintain (Most Common)

        SAP performs the authorization check.
        The object is automatically proposed when creating a role in PFCG.

        If set to Check/Maintain:
        - Object appears in PFCG role menu.
        - Security administrator maintains authorization values.
        - During execution, SAP checks whether the user has the required authorization.

        Ex: Standard business authorization objects that should be maintained in roles.

2. Check

        SAP performs the authorization check.
        Object is NOT automatically proposed in PFCG.

        If set to Check:
        - Runtime authorization check occurs.
        - Object is not automatically added to roles.

        Ex: Techncal objects, objects that should not be maintained by role administartor through standard role generation.

3. Do Not Check

        SAP does not perform the authorization check.
        Object is not proposed in PFCG.

        If set to Do Not Check:
        - Authorization check skipped

        Use Case
        - Remove unnecessary authorization checks.
        - Simplify role maintenance.
        - Used carefully because it can affect security.

                Ex: An authorization object exists in the program but is not required for your implementation.
